## 1. Overview & Core Concepts

This microservice is the **intelligent intermediary** between your domain applications and one or more LLM providers. It is designed as a **generic, pipeline-based platform** — rule refinement is the first pipeline, with the architecture ready to host any number of LLM workflows without structural change.

### What a Checkpoint Is

> A **Checkpoint** is a named **data quality standard** that an ingested rule is evaluated against **before** it reaches the LLM refinement stage. Checkpoints are declarative JSON specifications — non-developers can author and manage them without writing Java code.

Checkpoints answer: *“Is this rule good enough to be sent for refinement, and does it satisfy the required standards?”*

If a rule fails one or more checkpoints, **the failures are compiled into a structured feedback payload and passed directly to the LLM refinement request** so the model knows exactly what to fix.

### Checkpoint Scopes

|Scope                        |Description                                                    |Example                                               |
|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
|**Generic**                  |Global quality gates applied to every rule regardless of origin|Min length, no placeholder text, valid syntax         |
|**Enterprise**               |Standards owned by enterprise governance                       |Regulatory language compliance, mandatory clauses     |
|**Domain / Line-of-Business**|Standards for a specific business domain (Credit, Fraud, KYC)  |Domain-specific terminology, required field references|
|**Rule-specific**            |Overrides or additions tied to one particular rule             |Custom constraint for a legacy rule                   |

### Scalability Vision

```
Current Pipeline:   Rule Intake → Checkpoint Evaluation → Rule Refinement → Output
Future Pipelines:   Document Summarization Pipeline
                    Entity Extraction Pipeline
                    Policy Classification Pipeline
                    Risk Scoring Pipeline
                    ... (registered via PipelineRegistry)
```

Every pipeline shares the same infrastructure: checkpoint evaluation, prompt assembly, LLM routing, structured response parsing, and traceability.

