### 6.2 Scope Resolution

The engine resolves all applicable checkpoints for a rule before evaluating any of them:

```
CheckpointEvaluationEngine.resolveFor(rule)
    │
    ├── 1. All GENERIC checkpoints               (always included)
    ├── 2. ENTERPRISE checkpoints where
    │       scopeOwnerId == rule.enterpriseId
    ├── 3. DOMAIN checkpoints where
    │       scopeOwnerId == rule.domainId
    └── 4. RULE checkpoints where
            scopeOwnerId == rule.id.toString()

Merged list sorted by evaluationOrder ascending before execution.
```

### 6.3 Checkpoint Evaluation Engine

```java
// checkpoint/evaluator/CheckpointEvaluationEngine.java
@Service
public class CheckpointEvaluationEngine {

    private final CheckpointRegistry registry;
    private final Map<String, CheckpointEvaluator> evaluators; // keyed by evaluationType

    public CheckpointEvaluationReport evaluate(Rule rule) {
        var applicable = registry.resolveFor(rule);
        var failures   = new ArrayList<CheckpointFailure>();

        for (var checkpoint : applicable) {
            var result = evaluators
                .get(checkpoint.evaluationType())
                .evaluate(rule, checkpoint);

            if (!result.passed()) {
                failures.add(new CheckpointFailure(
                    checkpoint.id(),
                    checkpoint.name(),
                    checkpoint.scope(),
                    checkpoint.severity(),
                    result.failureReason(),
                    result.evaluatedValue()
                ));
            }
        }

        boolean hasBlocking = failures.stream()
            .anyMatch(f -> f.severity() == CheckpointSeverity.BLOCKING);

        return new CheckpointEvaluationReport(
            rule.id(), applicable.size(),
            applicable.size() - failures.size(),
            failures.size(), hasBlocking, failures,
            Instant.now()
        );
    }
}
```

### 6.4 Built-in Evaluator Types

|`evaluationType`|Parameters                                         |Behaviour                                                                                           |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`LENGTH`        |`minLength`, `maxLength`, `field`                  |Checks character length of the specified field                                                      |
|`REGEX`         |`prohibitedPatterns` or `requiredPatterns`, `field`|Matches patterns; fails if prohibited found or required missing                                     |
|`CONTAINS`      |`requiredTerms`, `minMatches`, `field`             |Asserts at least `minMatches` of `requiredTerms` are present                                        |
|`LLM_EVAL`      |`judgePrompt`, `model`                             |Sends rule + judgePrompt to a lightweight LLM judge; expects `{"pass": true/false, "reason": "..."}`|
|`CUSTOM_EXPR`   |`expression`                                       |Evaluates a Spring Expression Language (SpEL) expression against the `Rule` record                  |

### 6.5 Feedback Builder

```java
// checkpoint/feedback/RefinementFeedbackBuilder.java
@Component
public class RefinementFeedbackBuilder {

    public RefinementFeedback build(Rule rule, CheckpointEvaluationReport report) {
        if (!report.hasBlockingFailures()) {
            return RefinementFeedback.none(rule.id());
        }

        var blockingFailures = report.failures().stream()
            .filter(f -> f.severity() == CheckpointSeverity.BLOCKING)
            .toList();

        return new RefinementFeedback(
            rule.id(),
            true,
            blockingFailures,
            buildNarrative(blockingFailures)
        );
    }

    private String buildNarrative(List<CheckpointFailure> failures) {
        var sb = new StringBuilder(
            "The following data quality standards were not met. " +
            "You MUST rewrite the rule to satisfy each one:\n\n");

        for (int i = 0; i < failures.size(); i++) {
            var f = failures.get(i);
            sb.append(String.format(
                "%d. [%s] %s\n   Issue: %s\n   Problematic value: \"%s\"\n\n",
                i + 1, f.scope(), f.checkpointName(),
                f.failureReason(), f.evaluatedValue()
            ));
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
