## 15. Security Considerations

|Concern             |Approach                                                                                      |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Authentication      |JWT bearer; `ROLE_LLM_USER` for pipeline execution, `ROLE_LLM_ADMIN` for checkpoint management|
|API Keys            |Provider keys via env vars or HashiCorp Vault — never in code or config files                 |
|Checkpoint authoring|`POST/PUT /api/v1/checkpoints` requires `ROLE_LLM_ADMIN`                                      |
|PII in rule content |PII detection on `canonicalContent` before LLM call; offending fields masked in traces        |
|Prompt injection    |`canonicalContent` sanitized before template binding — strips control characters              |
|Audit               |`ExecutionTrace` records are append-only; JWT actor identity recorded on each trace           |
|Rate limiting       |Bucket4j per API key; pipeline execution and checkpoint management use separate limits        |

