## 17. Adding a New LLM Pipeline

The service is built to grow. Adding a new pipeline (e.g., document summarization) requires only these steps — no changes to any shared infrastructure.

**Step 1 — Add to the pipeline type enum**

```java
public enum PipelineType {
    RULE_REFINEMENT,
    SUMMARIZATION      // ← add here
}
```

**Step 2 — Implement the Pipeline interface**

```java
@Component
public class SummarizationPipeline implements Pipeline<SummarizationInput, SummarizationOutput> {

    @Override
    public PipelineType type() { return PipelineType.SUMMARIZATION; }

    @Override
    public PipelineResult execute(PipelineContext<SummarizationInput> ctx) {
        // Uses same shared services:
        // CheckpointEvaluationEngine, PromptAssembler, LlmRouter,
        // JsonResponseParser, TraceService
    }
}
```

**Step 3 — Add prompt templates**

```
resources/prompts/templates/summarization.mustache
```

**Step 4 — Add checkpoints if needed (JSON only, no Java)**

```
resources/checkpoints/domain/operations/summary-length.json
```

**Step 5 — Add test scenarios**

```
test/resources/llm/scenarios/summarization-scenario-01.json
```

The `PipelineRegistry` discovers the new `@Component` automatically via Spring’s component scan. The `PipelineExecutor` routes to it by `PipelineType` with no code change.

